National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location:
WYNDMERE, ND
Accident Number:
DEN84LA206
Date & Time:
07/01/1984, 0810 CDT 
Registration:
N4638
Aircraft:
GRUMMAN G-164A
Aircraft Damage:
Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries:
1 None
Flight Conducted Under:
Part 137: Agricultural
Analysis 
SOD WAS WORN FROM THE MIDDLE OF THE STRIP & THE STRIP WAS WET. 
THEREFORE, THE PLT ELECTED TO USE THE LEFT SIDE OF THE SOD STRIP FOR 
TAKEOFF. DURING THE TAKEOFF ROLL, THE LEFT SPRAY BOOM DRAGGED INTO 
WHEAT THAT WAS GROWING BESIDE THE RWY & THE ACFT VEERED LEFT. STRIPS OF 
WHEAT ABOUT 30 FT WIDE HAD BEEN PLANTED ON EACH SIDE OF THE RWY. AFTER 
CROSSING THE WHEAT, THE ACFT WENT INTO A WET BEAN FIELD & NOSED OVER. 
THE PLT WAS UNAWARE THAT THE BOOM HAD DRAGGED IN THE WHEAT & VEERED 
THE ACFT UNTIL AFTER THE ACCIDENT. 
Probable Cause and Findings
The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be:
